---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About — ReelShift"
	description="ReelShift is a free, browser-based video converter. Learn how it works and why it's free."
	canonicalPath="/about"
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
		<h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[#2B2013]">
			About ReelShift
		</h1>
		<div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-[#5C4F3D]">
			<p>
				ReelShift is a single-purpose tool for converting video files between
				MP4, WebM, GIF, and MP3 — entirely inside your web browser, using a
				real build of FFmpeg compiled to WebAssembly. No file you select is
				ever uploaded to a server.
			</p>
			<p>
				Because there is no server-side processing, ReelShift can stay
				completely free with no account, no watermark, and no file-size
				games. The site is supported by on-page advertising.
			</p>
			<p>
				Larger files can take longer to convert on older devices, since the
				work happens on your own hardware rather than in the cloud. The first
				conversion on a given visit downloads a small (~30MB) engine that is
				then cached by your browser for every conversion after that.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
